Repair works are currently ongoing at the National Assembly entrance gate after yesterday’s invasion by members of the Islamic Movement of Nigeria (IMN). Our correspondents saw engineers, welders and others at work, trying to fix a section of the entrance gate badly damaged yesterday by the protesting Shi’ites. Recall that Shi’ites protesters stormed National Assembly yesterday in protest against the continued detention of their leader, Ibrahim El-Zakzaky. Reps adjourn as Shiites threaten to pull down N/Assembly gate N/Assembly staff may disrupt Buhari’s budget presentation Just in: Security men, workers block National Assembly gate